subhead: Nearing its 25th anniversary, the online encyclopedia faces multiple challenges: accusations of 'woke' bias, threats to contributors, AI-generated content and declining readership. Despite these issues, Wikipedia remains resilient. But for how long?

title: Senate approves bill to end US shutdown, sending it to the House

title: Poppies and cornflowers became symbols of November 11 thanks to women forgotten by history
subhead: Every year on the anniversary of the 1918 Armistice, English-speaking countries traditionally wear a poppy, while the French don a cornflower. The origins of this custom, intended to raise funds for wounded war veterans, are rooted in a little-known history.

On the Syrian Golan Heights, Israel uses the same tools of repression as in the West Bank
subhead: Israel took advantage of the fall of the Assad regime to expand the area of southern Syria it has occupied since 1967. With uprootings of olive trees, arbitrary arrests and mobile checkpoints, soldiers have imposed a similar regime to that enforced on the population of the Palestinian territory.

title: François Ozon: 'No matter how big or small the film, I have always followed my own desire'
subhead: 'I wouldn't be where I am today if...' In this series, Le Monde interviews a figure about a decisive moment in their life. As a child, the director of 'The Stranger' discovered the world through his father's Super 8 films.

title: Jean-François Bayart, sociologist: 'Gen Z embodies an ambivalent protest'
subhead: The French sociologist explains how the recent wave of youth mobilization is a reaction to the conservative revolution, the mixture of authoritarianism and economic predation to which many states are succumbing. He notes, however, that this wave is not without its ideological ambiguities.
